arget is also poisoned. If the Poison succeeds on an attack roll (1d20+8) against the target's\u00a0Fortitude Defense, the target takes 2d6 points of damage and moves -1 step along the\u00a0Condition Track. If the attack fails, the target takes half damage and doesn't move on the\u00a0Condition Track. Kinrath Poison attacks each round until cured with a DC 18\u00a0Treat Injury\u00a0check.","derived":{}},"effects":[],"flags":{"swse":{"beastData":{"name":"Viper Kinrath","cl":7,"tags":["beast"],"size":"large","initiative":7,"senses":"Blind,\u00a0Perception: +10","perception":null,"reflexDefense":17,"flatFootedDefense":14,"fortitudeDefense":16,"willDefense":11,"hitPoints":84,"damageThreshold":21,"speed":"6 Squares","melee":"Slam +10 (1d6+8)","fightingSpace":"2x2 Squares","reach":"1 Square","baseAttackBonus":6,"grapple":15,"speciesTraits":[],"abilities":{"strength":18,"dexterity":16,"constitution":22,"intelligence":1,"wisdom":13,"charisma":6},"feats":["7146640744fdf052","05459ac4d439f229","ecc2471ac96ec2d4"],"skills":["Perception\u00a0+10"],"abilityText":"Blind:\u00a0Viper Kinrath are Blind and take no penalties due to\u00a0Concealment\u00a0and\u00a0Total Concealment\u00a0due to darkness. They use a variety of other senses to identify their enemies.\nPoison:\u00a0If a Viper Kinrath deals damage with its Sting attack to a living target, the target is also poisoned. If the Poison succeeds on an attack roll (1d20+8) against the target's\u00a0Fortitude Defense, the target takes 2d6 points of damage and moves -1 step along the\u00a0Condition Track. If the attack fails, the target takes half damage and doesn't move on the\u00a0Condition Track. Kinrath Poison attacks each round until cured with a DC 18\u00a0Treat Injury\u00a0check.","beastLevel":8}}},"items":[]}
