include the nearest ally in an attack on this turn.\nIf the attack against the target's\u00a0Will Defense\u00a0misses, the target may act normally. If the attack misses by 5 or more, the target shakes off the madness and is no longer subject to this effect. This is a\u00a0Mind-Affecting\u00a0effect.\nRegenerate:\u00a0When a T'salak reaches 0 or fewer Hit Points, it does not die. It becomes an inert puddle for a number of rounds equal to half its maximum Hit Points (rounded down), after which the T'salak regenerates 1 Hit Point per round until fully healed. It cannot Regenerate in a\u00a0Vacuum\u00a0nor while contained inside a Force-blocking item.","derived":{}},"effects":[],"flags":{"swse":{"beastData":{"name":"T'salak","cl":7,"tags":["beast"],"size":"medium","initiative":8,"senses":"Darkvision,\u00a0Perception\u00a0+6","perception":6,"reflexDefense":14,"flatFootedDefense":10,"fortitudeDefense":12,"willDefense":12,"hitPoints":50,"damageThreshold":12,"speed":"8 Squares","melee":"Tendril +10 (1d8+4); Tendril +8 (2d8+4) with\u00a0Rapid Strike","fightingSpace":"1 Square","reach":"1 Square","baseAttackBonus":6,"grapple":10,"speciesTraits":[],"abilities":{"strength":10,"dexterity":18,"constitution":14,"intelligence":2,"wisdom":14,"charisma":12},"feats":["ddbeb23013d9e917","ccb33e58342499a3","a9f6de36f24ef202","252b67d6e31c377e"],"skills":["Climb\u00a0+9 (may reroll, may keep better result),\u00a0Stealth\u00a0+13"],"abilityText":"Induce Raging Madness:\u00a0Whenever this creature damages a target with a melee attack, it infuses the target with raging madness. At the beginning of the target's turn, the madness makes an attack against the\u00a0Will Defense\u00a0of the target at +11. If the attack succeeds, the target must include the nearest ally in an attack on this turn.\nIf the attack against the target's\u00a0Will Defense\u00a0misses, the target may act normally. If the attack misses by 5 or more, the target shakes off the madness and is no longer subject to this effect. This is a\u00a0Mind-Affecting\u00a0effect.\nRegenerate:\u00a0When a T'salak reaches 0 or fewer Hit Points, it does not die. It becomes an inert puddle for a number of rounds equal to half its maximum Hit Points (rounded down), after which the T'salak regenerates 1 Hit Point per round until fully healed. It cannot Regenerate in a\u00a0Vacuum\u00a0nor while contained inside a Force-blocking item.","beastLevel":8}}},"items":[]}
